<task id="d3f666f9edad82a" xml:lang="en-US">
    <title>Downloading the DITA-OP Editor</title>
    <prolog>
        <author>claude</author>
    </prolog>
    <taskbody>
        <context>
            To download the DITA-OP Editor plugins you may choose one of
            the following options.
        </context>
    </taskbody>
    <task id="bf3e678e623b8427">
        <title>Downloading the full package</title>
        <taskbody>
            <context>
                <p>
                    This package includes the Eclipse IDE for windows,
                    the DITA-OP plugins (and their dependencies), the
                    CVS plugin and
                    <xref href="http://subclipse.tigris.org/"
                        scope="external" type="html">
                        Subclipse, the SVN team plugin.
                    </xref>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Work is still needed on this package to remove
                    things that are not becessary to a typical technical
                    writer but it is a good start if you do not use
                    Eclipse already and want to evaluate the editor.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Also, it is only available for windows and if demand
                    is high enough for other platforms we will build
                    other packages. In the mean time, if you are using
                    another platform please
                    <xref scope="external" type="html"
                        href="http://www.eclipse.org/downloads/">
                        download the Eclipse IDE for your platform
                    </xref>
                    and use one the other download methods.
                </p>
            </context>
            <steps>
                <step>
                    <cmd>
                        Go to the
                        <xref scope="external" type="html"
                            href="http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=228491&amp;package_id=276725">
                            project's download page.
                        </xref>
                    </cmd>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <cmd>
                        Choose the
                        <filepath>
                            doped-1.0.0.M1-20080618-win32.zip
                        </filepath>
                        zip file.
                    </cmd>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <cmd>
                        Unzip the file anywhere on your file system and
                        run the
                        <filepath>eclipse.exe</filepath>
                        file contained in the newly created
                        <filepath>doped-1.0.0.M1-20080618</filepath>
                        folder.
                    </cmd>
                </step>
            </steps>
        </taskbody>
    </task>
    <task id="a718ad80b006935">
        <title>Downloading the plugins zip file</title>
        <taskbody>
            <context>
                If you are already using Eclipse 3.3 (Europa) you can
                download the plugins zip file.
            </context>
            <steps>
                <step>
                    <cmd>
                        Go to the
                        <xref scope="external" type="html"
                            href="http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=228491&amp;package_id=276725">
                            project's download page.
                        </xref>
                    </cmd>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <cmd>
                        Choose the
                        <filepath>
                            org.dita_op_1.0.0.M1-20080618-bin.zip
                        </filepath>
                        zip file.
                    </cmd>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <cmd>
                        Once downloaded, unzip the file in the Eclipse
                        folder (the one which contains the
                        <filepath>features</filepath>
                        and
                        <filepath>plugins</filepath>
                        folders).
                    </cmd>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <cmd>If necessary, restart Eclipse.</cmd>
                </step>
            </steps>
        </taskbody>
    </task>
    <task id="b1571f23a914bd39">
        <title>Using the update site</title>
        <task id="d221538040e5a9d0">
            <title>Eclipse 3.3 (Europa)</title>
            <taskbody>
                <context>
                    If you are already using Eclipse 3.3 you can use the
                    Update Manager to download and install the plugins
                    for you.
                </context>
                <steps>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Open Eclipse, go to
                            <menucascade>
                                <uicontrol>Help</uicontrol>
                                <uicontrol>Software Updates</uicontrol>
                                <uicontrol>
                                    Find and Install...
                                </uicontrol>
                            </menucascade>
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Choose
                            <uicontrol>
                                Search for new features to install.
                            </uicontrol>
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Click on the
                            <uicontrol>"New Remote Site..."</uicontrol>
                            button.
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Enter
                            <userinput>DITA-OP Update Site</userinput>
                            in the
                            <uicontrol>name</uicontrol>
                            field.
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Enter
                            <userinput>
                                http://www.dita-op.org/updatesite
                            </userinput>
                            in the
                            <uicontrol>URL</uicontrol>
                            field.
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Click on the
                            <uicontrol>OK</uicontrol>
                            button.
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Make sure the
                            <uicontrol>DITA-OP Update Site</uicontrol>
                            check box is selected (you may have to
                            select the
                            <uicontrol>Europa Discovery Site</uicontrol>
                            as well to fetch dependencies).
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Click on the
                            <uicontrol>Finish</uicontrol>
                            button.
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Select the
                            <uicontrol>DITA-OP Update Site</uicontrol>
                            check box (if an error appears about missing
                            dependencies click on the
                            <uicontrol>Select Required</uicontrol>
                            button).
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Click on the
                            <uicontrol>Next</uicontrol>
                            button.
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Choose the
                            <uicontrol>
                                I accept the terms in the license
                                agreement
                            </uicontrol>
                            radio button.
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Click on the
                            <uicontrol>Next</uicontrol>
                            button.
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Click on the
                            <uicontrol>Finish</uicontrol>
                            button.
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>Wait for the download to complete.</cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Click on the
                            <uicontrol>Install</uicontrol>
                            button.
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Click on the
                            <uicontrol>Yes</uicontrol>
                            button to restart Eclipse.
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                </steps>
            </taskbody>
        </task>
        <task id="a10ef80e8958cc03">
            <title>Eclipse 3.4 (Ganymede)</title>
            <prolog>
                <author>Richard Pineger</author>
            </prolog>
            <taskbody>
                <context>
                    Eclipse 3.4 has an updated Update Manager called P2
                    and so the process is slightly different. Thanks to
                    Richard Pineger for the following install
                    instructions.
                </context>
                <steps>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Open Eclipse, go to
                            <menucascade>
                                <uicontrol>Help</uicontrol>
                                <uicontrol>
                                    Software Updates...
                                </uicontrol>
                            </menucascade>
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Select the
                            <uicontrol>Available Software</uicontrol>
                            tab.
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Click
                            <uicontrol>Add Site...</uicontrol>
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            In the
                            <uicontrol>Add Site</uicontrol>
                            dialog, enter
                            <userinput>
                                http://www.dita-op.org/updatesite
                            </userinput>
                            in the
                            <uicontrol>Location</uicontrol>
                            field.
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Click the
                            <uicontrol>OK</uicontrol>
                            button.
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Make sure the
                            <uicontrol>
                                http://www.dita-op.org/updatesite
                            </uicontrol>
                            check box and
                            <uicontrol>Uncategorized</uicontrol>
                            check boxes are selected.
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Click the
                            <uicontrol>Install...</uicontrol>
                            button.
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Wait for the Update Manager to resolves
                            dependencies.
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Read and accept the necessary license
                            agreements.
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Wait for the download and install to
                            complete.
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <cmd>
                            Click on the
                            <uicontrol>Yes</uicontrol>
                            button to restart Eclipse.
                        </cmd>
                    </step>
                </steps>
            </taskbody>
        </task>
    </task>
    <task id="ea4a36c1690532b3">
        <title>Nightly builds</title>
        <taskbody>
            <context>
                Nightly builds are available at
                <xref scope="external" type="html"
                    href="http://www.pluginbuilder.org">
                    pluginbuilder.org
                </xref>
                you can either download the latest plugins zip file
                <xref scope="external" type="html"
                    href="http://dita-op.pluginbuilder.org/latest">
                    here
                </xref>
                or use the nightly builds' update site:
                <xref scope="external" type="html"
                    href="http://dita-op.pluginbuilder.org/nightly/updateSite">
                    http://dita-op.pluginbuilder.org/nightly/updateSite
                </xref>
            </context>
        </taskbody>
    </task>
    <task id="f499a3bdd3773136">
        <title>Downloading the sources</title>
        <taskbody>
            <context>
                <p>
                    To download the sources you can go to the
                    <xref scope="external" type="html"
                        href="http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=228491&amp;package_id=276725">
                        project's download page
                    </xref>
                    and choose the
                    <filepath>
                        org.dita_op_1.0.0.M1-20080618-src.zip
                    </filepath>
                    zip file which contains both the binaries and the
                    sources.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Or you can download the sources from the SVN source
                    repository. The repository URL is
                    <xref scope="external" type="html"
                        href="http://svn.dita-op.org/svnroot/dita-op/">
                        http://svn.dita-op.org/svnroot/dita-op/
                    </xref>
                    and is anonymously accessible.
                </p>
                <p>
                    You can refer to this sourceforge page for detailed
                    information about SVN:
                    <xref scope="external" type="html"
                        href="http://alexandria.wiki.sourceforge.net/Subversion+-+Version+Control+for+Source+Code">
                        Subversion - Version Control for Source Code.
                    </xref>
                </p>
            </context>
        </taskbody>
    </task>
</task>